The Vita Field Programmable Gate Array Logic Block has two registers.
The IO register, and the Look Up Table register. The IO register
stores three bits, and the Look Up Table register stores four bits.
The IO register has six valid values that it can have, and those
range from 000 to 101. When the IO register has the value of 110 or
111, the Logic Block basically becomes a no-op.

When the IO register has the value of 000, the IONorth pin is the
most significant bit of the Look Up Table register and the IOEast
pin is the least significant bit of the Look Up Table register. The
IOSouth and IOWest pins both output the same 1 bit output from
whatever 2-bit address is looked up in the Look Up Table register.

When the IO register has the value of 001, the IOEast pin is the
most significant bit of the Look Up Table register and the IOSouth
pin is the least significant bit of the Look Up Table register. The
IOWest and IONorth pins both output the same 1 bit output from
whatever 2-bit address is looked up in the Look Up Table register.

When the IO register has the value of 010, the IOSouth pin is the
most significant bit of the Look Up Table register and the IOWest
pin is the least significant bit of the Look Up Table register. The
IONorth and IOEast pins both output the same 1 bit output from
whatever 2-bit address is looked up in the Look Up Table register.

When the IO register has the value of 011, the IOWest pin is the
most significant bit of the Look Up Table register and the IONorth
pin is the least significant bit of the Look Up Table register. The
IOEast and IOSouth pins both output the same 1 bit output from
whatever 2-bit address is looked up in the Look Up Table register.

When the IO register has the value of 100, the IONorth pin is the
most significant bit of the Look Up Table register and the IOSouth
pin is the least significant bit of the Look Up Table register. The
IOEast and IOWest pins both output the same 1 bit output from
whatever 2-bit address is looked up in the Look Up Table register.

When the IO register has the value of 101, the IOEast pin is the
most significant bit of the Look Up Table register and the IOWest
pin is the least significant bit of the Look Up Table register. The
IONorth and IOSouth pins both output the same 1 bit output from
whatever 2-bit address is looked up in the Look Up Table register.

The Look Up Table Register can have it’s four bits be configured in a
way that allows for two inputs, two outputs, one input, two outputs
because one input is ignored, and zero inputs, two outputs because
two inputs are ignored.

